Workflow of MY Philosopher`s Program
====================================

1. Input Validation
Ensures that the program receives valid arguments before initializing the simulation..

validate_input(ac, av) â†’ Checks the number and validity of arguments.
check_numbers(ac, av) â†’ Iterates through arguments and verifies they are valid numbers.
is_number(str) â†’ Ensures the string contains only numeric characters.
is_valid_number(num, index) â†’ Checks if the number falls within the valid range.

ğŸ“„ File: validation.c

2. Structures Initialization & Thread/Mutex Creation
Initializes core data structures, mutexes, and threads.

init_admin(ac, av) â†’ Oversees data initialization and thread creation.
init_data(data, ac, av) â†’ Allocates memory and initializes program parameters.
init_data_mutexes(data) â†’ Initializes global mutexes (e.g., print_lock, death_lock).
init_forks(data) â†’ Assigns a fork mutex to each philosopher.
init_philosophers(data) â†’ Sets initial values for each philosopher.
init_threads(data) â†’ Creates threads for philosophers and monitoring.

ğŸ“Œ Prepares all necessary data structures before starting the simulation.
ğŸ“„ File: initialization.câ€‹

Main()
